nts1.d: Sublime and rain-slicked mood music, emotional trance-indebted soundscapes and other soundtrack cuts from the world of Masamune Shirow's anime and manga series Ghost In The Shell - a cyberpunk classic that rang alarming bells about the progress of technology, and asked dark and deep questions about what it means to be human.

slow + spacious sentimental/hopecore vibes in lieu of my recent move to berlin.

Artist, graphic designer and DJ Paul Camo sets out to push the boundaries: free of all restrictions. Jump in the chat and listen as Paul Camo's WE ARE brings you on a voyage through the spectrum of jazz fusion, spiritual jazz, experimental jazz and everything in between.

nts2.d: Veronica Vasicka presents a monthly 2-hour show featuring the lost synth-wave treasures she has archived from the late 70s and early 80s, along with other iconic underground electronic music drawn from over four decades. Expect to hear exclusive tracks from releases on her seminal Minimal Wave and Cititrax labels plus cassette-only and private press rarities.

Chicago-based archival record label, The Numero Group, host a deep-digging once a month show. Expect comprehensive round ups from their crates, picking out the best old music and reissues, as well as some jubilant nerdy record chat.

A five-part series from Baltimore hardcore band Turnstile, with each band member curating and presenting a personal selection of music on NTS.
Picture by Alex Henery

nts2.d:
Aotearoa/New Zealand based Flying Nun Records present a monthly show of hidden gems and classics from the Nun catalogue, the nu-wave of the New Zealand underground and other curiosities from further afield.
Join a revolving cast of Flying Nun alumni & friends for this monthly deep dive into the label's history and beyond.
Coinciding with the release of his new Venamoris album out on 28th February, Dave Lombardo - best known as drummer in Slayer, Dead Cross & Mr Bungle - plays music that influenced the new release.

Music will be played once a month.

Enter Radha's spiritual soundscape - of special tunes near and dear to her.

subtle.d: Japanese DJ from Tokyo, currently living in London.  Based on UK club music, but straddles other genres such as dancehall, reggaeton, gqom and amapiano.

Hailing from northern Italy, STANDARD is a collective of artists, DJs and producers that aims at the promotion of bass music: Garage, UK Funky, Breaks, Leftfield Bass, Leftfield Techno, Dubstep, everything in between and beyond. They focus on the Italian Bass scene, showcasing new up-and-coming artists as well as established talents from all over the peninsula.

Oddkut is a producer & DJ hailing from Balakovo City, Russia. He's part of the Russian collective "United Gang" who are a Moscow-based community of local musicians, DJ's and promoters teamed up by their genuine love & interest in UK underground music, "TAЭT VREMYA" art group and the creator of the Moscow parties "Judder".

Kishan is a DJ and Producer currently based in London. Actively involved in the music scene already, he produces and mixes a wide range of genres including UK Garage, Drum & Bass, House, Disco and Afrobeat.
